OL,3,CRail services grind to standstill as
OL,4,Cpay dispute nears two years
OL,6,FAslef general secretary Mick Whelan
OL,7,Fsaid his members remained solidly
OL,8,Fbehind the industrial action, and
OL,9,Fcriticised the Government and rail
OL,10,Fcompanies for the lack of contact over
OL,11,Fthe past year.
OL,13,FThe Rail Delivery Group says it's open
OL,14,Fto talks with ASLEF and wants to work
OL,15,Fwith them to resolve the dispute.
